# delete_irida_sequence_file
# delete a sequencing object from a sample in IRIDA
#
# usage: delete_irida_sequence_file PROJECT_ID SAMPLE_ID OBJECT_TYPE OBJECT_ID
#
# OBJECT_TYPE: unpaired | pairs | fast5
# OBJECT_ID: sequencing object ID (not the file ID)
#
# NOTE: the documented path DELETE /api/samples/{id}/sequenceFiles/{fileId} is wrong.
# The correct path is DELETE /api/samples/{sampleId}/{objectType}/{objectId}.
# The documented path passes a file ID where a sequencing object ID is expected,
# causing a NullPointerException in readSequencingObjectForSample. Root cause confirmed
# from RESTSampleSequenceFilesController.java line 696. See GitHub issue #4.
#
# NOTE: confirmed working as non-admin on VIGASP 23.01.3. RBAC gap - see GitHub issue #12.
#
# example: delete_irida_sequence_file 150:test_gmarselis 11745:ZZTEST_SAMPLE_DO_NOT_USE unpaired 11998
